---
// Two-track fork beneath the hero: one shared thesis (set by the hero above),
// two parallel products.
//
// GROUNDING NOTES for downstream editors / fact-checkers:
// (a) "Promptless Instruction Governance" is a DERIVED, NOT-LOCKED public label
//     (from the strategy doc's "Agent Instruction Governance"). It still needs a
//     name/tagline lock — do not treat this wording as final.
// (b) The Instruction Governance blurb is VISION/CAPABILITY-level only. The
//     analyzer is partly pre-launch: no "available now"/"today"/GA claims here.
// (c) No customer social proof in this section (no named logos, quotes, or
//     implied customers).
---

<section class="pl-two-tracks not-content" data-section-tracked="tracks">
  <ul class="pl-two-tracks-grid">
    <li class="pl-two-tracks-card">
      <p class="pl-two-tracks-label">
        Promptless for Docs
        <span class="pl-two-tracks-tag pl-two-tracks-tag-live">Available now</span>
      </p>
      <p class="pl-two-tracks-blurb">
        For your external, customer-facing docs. When your product changes, Promptless drafts the
        updates — following your style guide, refreshing screenshots, and fitting your existing
        toolchain. You review, edit, and ship.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li class="pl-two-tracks-card">
      <p class="pl-two-tracks-label">
        Promptless Instruction Governance
        <span class="pl-two-tracks-tag">Coming soon</span>
      </p>
      <!-- IG copy is vision/capability-level only — no availability/GA claim.
           The "Coming soon" tag is the not-yet-available signal; keep blurb in
           forthcoming ("will") framing. -->
      <p class="pl-two-tracks-blurb">
        Promptless Instruction Governance will treat your internal agent instructions —
        AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, and Skills — as governed documentation: inventorying them,
        surfacing findings when they go stale, missing, or contradictory, and proposing
        corrections. You'll see every finding before anything changes.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<style>
  .pl-two-tracks {
    padding: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-grid {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-card {
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-label {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-tag {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #eef2ff;
    color: #506aea;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-tag-live {
    background: #ecfdf5;
    color: #047857;
  }

  .pl-two-tracks-blurb {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #4b5563;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pl-two-tracks-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
